title: Reading Data
text: There are different types of data, we won’t get into the nitty-gritty parts of it, but there is structured, semi-structured, and ustructured data. We will be playing around with structured data (think excel files). Examples of the other types of data are pictures, video, and audio files.

Course Outline:
Installation What kind of data are we using? Reading in data - BaseR and Tidyverse - there’s a from readr option using the “import dataset” option from the environment pane Wrangling data - dplyr, for data manipulation - tidyr, for data tidying - cleaning, the difference between them all, and when they should all take place in the process Visualization of data - the glory of ggplot
